  "body": "### Description\r\n\r\n[comment]: # (Feature or Bug? i.e Type: Bug)\r\n*Type*: Bug\r\n\r\n[comment]: # (Describe the feature you would like, or briefly summarise the bug and what you did, what you expected to happen, and what actually happens. Sections below)\r\n*Summary*: \r\nIf type 2 lines of text and move to Chats and back to the chat then these 2 lines are in the input field and 1st line is cut. Expected: both lines are fully visible\r\n![reopen chat with text](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/6584810/26055604/e6c62f1c-3971-11e7-8223-1be2984e219c.png)\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n#### Expected behavior\r\n[comment]: # (Describe what you expected to happen.)\r\nBoth lines of text are fully visible\r\n#### Actual behavior\r\n[comment]: # (Describe what actually happened.)\r\nFirst line of text is cut on the top\r\n### Reproduction\r\n[comment]: # (Describe how we can replicate the bug step by step.)\r\nVideo: https://drive.google.com/open?id=0Bz3t9zSg1wb7ak85NGt4UkhrSUk\r\n- Open Status\r\n- Open 1-1 chat\r\n- type \"One line\" and tap on enter on device keyboard. As a result, new line is started. Check the visibility of first line.\r\n- Type text \"second line\" and do not send it\r\n- Move to Chats\r\n- Open 1-1 chat again. Check the visibility of first line in the input field\r\n\r\n\r\n### Additional Information\r\n[comment]: # (Please do your best to fill this out.)\r\n* Status version: 0.9.7\r\n* Operating System: Android and iOS\r\n\r\n",
